  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Strong\" title=\"House Strong\"><img alt=\"House Strong.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/50px-House_Strong.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/75px-House_Strong.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/36/House_Strong.svg/100px-House_Strong.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Robert Strong</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\"><img alt=\"Kingsguard.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/50px-Kingsguard.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/75px-Kingsguard.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6d/Kingsguard.svg/100px-Kingsguard.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Ser_robert_strong.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ser robert strong.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/74/Ser_robert_strong.jpg/350px-Ser_robert_strong.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"477\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/74/Ser_robert_strong.jpg/525px-Ser_robert_strong.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/74/Ser_robert_strong.jpg/700px-Ser_robert_strong.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Ser Robert Strong, art by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.deviantart.com/art/Ser-Robert-Strong-365909658\">Robert O'Leary</a> ©.</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>The silent giant<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Qyburn's mute monster<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafrobert_strong.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafrobert_strong.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Robert Strong</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> acquainted to <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a>. A giant of a man, eight feet tall, he has been appointed to the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and will fight for <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> in her <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Robert\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Robert</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Robert_Strong\" title=\"Category:Images of Robert Strong\">Images of Robert Strong</a></div>\n<p>Robert is eight feet tall, with legs as thick as trees, a chest worthy of a plow <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horse</a>, and shoulders that would not disgrace an ox. His <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a> is <a href=\"/index.php/Steel\" title=\"Steel\">steel</a> plate enameled white, over <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gilded</a> mail. A <a href=\"/index.php/Greathelm\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Greathelm\">greathelm</a> hides his face, with seven <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silken</a> plumes in the rainbow colors of the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith</a> streaming from the crest. A pair of golden seven-pointed stars clasp his white cloak to his shoulders.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser Robert never shows his face, hiding it constantly under his greathelm. He apparently has no physiological necessities, consuming neither food nor drink nor needing to excrete.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to Qyburn, Ser Robert has made a <a href=\"/index.php/Vow_of_silence\" title=\"Vow of silence\">vow of silence</a>, supposedly one of not speaking until <i>\"all of [King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen</a>'s] enemies are dead and evil has been driven from the realm\"</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> dies of a <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poisoned</a> wound, screaming in the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_cells\" title=\"Black cells\">black cells</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Keep\" title=\"Red Keep\">Red Keep</a>, under the care of the former <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> who had been expelled from the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a> for unethical experiments and studying <a href=\"/index.php/Necromancy\" title=\"Necromancy\">necromancy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc7.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Qyburn sends the <a href=\"/index.php/Mountain%27s_skull\" title=\"Mountain&#39;s skull\">Mountain's skull</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, as ordered.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Loras_Tyrell\" title=\"Loras Tyrell\">Loras Tyrell</a> leaves for the <a href=\"/index.php/Siege_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Siege of Dragonstone\">siege of Dragonstone</a>, Qyburn suggests to Queen Regent <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> that the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> may need a replacement in case Loras dies, and mentions a \"champion\" who \"no living man will be able to withstand\". Qyburn orders a massive suit of <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a> for his proposed champion, though it is supposedly too large and heavy to be worn by any man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>After Cersei is arrested by the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a> for adultery and other crimes, Qyburn tells her that his champion is ready, to defend Cersei and prove her innocence in battle. However, Cersei informs Qyburn that as a queen, she can only be represented in a <a href=\"/index.php/Trial_by_combat\" title=\"Trial by combat\">trial by combat</a> by a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of the Kingsguard, and there are no open positions available.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc43.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:351px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5c/Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png/349px-Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png\" width=\"349\" height=\"260\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5c/Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png/524px-Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png 1.5x, /images/5/5c/Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Alexandre_Dainche_Ser_Robert_Strong.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser Robert Strong, by Alexandre Dainche © FFG</div></div></div>\n<p>Cersei learns that Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arys_Oakheart\" title=\"Arys Oakheart\">Arys Oakheart</a> of the Kingsguard has died in <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>. She tells her uncle, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Regent\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lord Regent\">Lord Regent</a>, to bring Qyburn a white cloak and have her son, King <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen Baratheon</a>, appoint the man Qyburn presents to the Kingsguard.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>When Queen Cersei arrives at the Red Keep after <a href=\"/index.php/Walk_of_atonement\" title=\"Walk of atonement\">walking naked</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Sept_of_Baelor\" title=\"Great Sept of Baelor\">Great Sept of Baelor</a>, Ser Robert Strong lifts her up and carries her into the castle. Qyburn introduces Robert to Cersei as her and her son's champion, which pleases her greatly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later, at a meeting of the <a href=\"/index.php/Small_council\" title=\"Small council\">small council</a>, Kevan announces that Cersei will be championed by Ser Robert Strong in her trial. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> grimaces at the idea, and Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a> demands to know who Ser Robert is and where he came from. Kevan remembers that Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Meryn_Trant\" title=\"Meryn Trant\">Meryn Trant</a> claimed that Robert took neither food nor water, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Boros_Blount\" title=\"Boros Blount\">Boros Blount</a> said he had never even seen him use the privy. Kevan has inexplicit suspicions about the <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">identity of the man</a>, suspicions he believes are shared by Mace and Randyll. However, Kevan makes clear to the small council that it is in everyone's best interests that Ser Robert's identity not be questioned and that he must prevail in Cersei's trial. If Ser Robert fails and Cersei is found guilty, Tommen's legitimacy as king and, thus, <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a>'s status as queen, would be thrown into question, hurting both <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tyrell\" title=\"House Tyrell\">House Tyrell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Robert\">Quotes about Robert</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Robert\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>What he lacks in gallantry he will give you tenfold in devotion. He will protect <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">your son</a>, kill your enemies, and keep your secrets, and no living man will be able to withstand him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Cersei:</b> When the hour is ripe, you may produce this paragon of yours and we will see if he is all that you have promised.<br />\n<b>Qyburn:</b> They will sing of him, I swear it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A white cloak. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan</a> had kept his part of the bargain. <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">Tommen</a>, her precious little boy, had named her champion to the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>If it please Your Grace, Ser Robert has taken a holy vow of silence. He has sworn that he will not speak until all of <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_Baratheon\" title=\"Tommen Baratheon\">His Grace's</a> enemies are dead and evil has been driven from the realm.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Qyburn\" title=\"Qyburn\">Qyburn</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Yes, thought Cersei Lannister. Oh, yes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Tell me, ser, where did this man come from? Why have we never heard his name before? He does not speak, he will not show his face, he is never seen without his <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a>. Do we know for a certainty that he is even a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a>?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We do not even know if he's alive.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Kevan_Lannister\" title=\"Kevan Lannister\">Kevan Lannister</a> had a strong suspicion of just <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">who this Ser Robert really was</a> beneath that gleaming white <a href=\"/index.php/Armor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Armor\">armor</a>. A suspicion that <a href=\"/index.php/Mace_Tyrell\" title=\"Mace Tyrell\">Mace Tyrell</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> no doubt shared. Whatever the face hidden behind Strong's <a href=\"/index.php/Helm\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Helm\">helm</a>, it must remain hidden for now. The silent giant was <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">his niece's</a> only hope. <i>And pray that he is as formidable as he appears</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theories\">Theories</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Theories\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>See <a href=\"/index.php/Robert_Strong/Theories\" title=\"Robert Strong/Theories\">Robert Strong/Theories</a>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Robert_Strong&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwdepilogue.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7